  "commentary": "With SPX at 6604.8 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6612 and right at the max positive gamma wall of 6605, dealers are likely selling into any bounce attempts here as they hedge their long gamma position. The PIN regime with massive positive GEX walls at 6605/6610/6620 creates a strong ceiling effect, while the negative gamma at 6590 provides a floor where dealers would flip to buying dips if breached. The recent wall break and GEX surge events suggest we just saw volatility expansion, but now price is gravitating back toward these major stabilizing levels.\n\nKey levels: 6612 flip strike as the regime boundary, 6605 max positive gamma for immediate resistance, and 6590 negative gamma support.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590-6610 with dealers capping upside moves.",
